pageContext.claim: “The unemployment rate just hit the lowest level in more than 50 years.”
pageContext.analysis: At the time of these remarks, the monthly unemployment rate was 3.7 percent, or the lowest since 1969 -- 49 years. In 1968, the unemployment rate dipped as low as 3.4 percent. We are including in the database the times when Trump claims the unemployment rate is the lowest in more than 50 years; if he just says 50 years, we will consider that an acceptable rounding-up of the number.
